        <abstract>
            <p>An entomologist who has been staying with CD [T. V. Wollaston] says the pupa she sent would turn into a lackey moth.</p>
            <p>Adds that the great destruction of birds in the winter preceding the last is probable cause of survival of caterpillars and resulting numerous cocoons.</p>
